# Databricks: Always Use odin_decrypt() for Encrypted Fields

When querying tables in `ued_salesforce_dwh` (or any Databricks schema with KEY_IDPS_SALESFORCE encrypted values), always wrap encrypted PII fields with `odin_decrypt()` to return readable plaintext.

## Commonly Encrypted Fields

- `name`, `firstname`, `lastname`, `email`, `phone`, `alias` on user/lead/contact/account tables

## Example

```sql
-- ✅ GOOD
SELECT odin_decrypt(u.name) AS owner_name
FROM ued_salesforce_dwh.sales_user u

-- ❌ BAD (returns encrypted tokens)
SELECT u.name AS owner_name
FROM ued_salesforce_dwh.sales_user u
```

## Important Limitation

- `odin_decrypt()` is a Hive UDF and only works on **interactive/job clusters**, NOT on SQL warehouses.
- If a query fails with `CANNOT_LOAD_FUNCTION_CLASS`, advise the user to run the query in a Databricks notebook attached to an interactive cluster.
